cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving neural machine translation models using subword regularization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also proposes a new subword segmentation algorithm based on a unigram language model, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The regularization method used in the paper is also related to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper experiments with multiple corpora, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) if the corpora are image-based.
